apter treats the basic theory of train tracks as discovered by W. P. Thurston, including recurrence, transverse recurrence, and the explicit construction of a measured geodesic lamination from a measured train track. The subsequent chapters develop certain material from R. C. Penner's thesis, including a natural equivalence relation on measured train tracks and standard models for the equivalence classes (which are used to analyze the topology and geometry of the space of measured geodesic laminations), a duality between transverse and tangential structures on a train track, and the explicit computation of the action of the mapping class group on the space of measured geodesic laminations in the surface.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aCW complexes. 0aCombinatorial analysis. 0aGeodesics (Mathematics). 7aMATHEMATICS / Combinatorics.2bisacsh  aAmbient isotopy.  aAnalytic function.  aAxiom.  aBrouwer fixed-point theorem.  aCW complex.  aCantor set.  aCardinality.  aChange of basis.  aCoefficient.  aCombinatorics.  aCompactification (mathematics).  aConjugacy class.  aConnected component (graph theory).  aConnectivity (graph theory).  aCoordinate system.  aCotangent space.  aCovering space.  aDeformation theory.  aDehn twist.  aDiffeomorphism.  aDifferential topology.  aDisjoint sets.  aDisjoint union.  aDisk (mathematics).  aEigenvalues and eigenvectors.  aEmbedding.  aEquation.  aEquivalence class (music).  aEquivalence class.  aEquivalence relation.  aEuclidean space.  aEuler characteristic.  aExplicit formula.  aExplicit formulae (L-function).  aFiber bundle.  aFoliation.  aFuchsian group.  aGeodesic curvature.  aGeometry.  aHarmonic function.  aHomeomorphism.  aHomotopy.  aHorocycle.  aHyperbolic geometry.  aHyperbolic moti